# 📂 03 — Production

**Business function:** Background Art Production — 2D Animation Studio
**Trigger:** P05 colour key brief approved by art director — artist begins active background painting
**Prompts in this section:** P06, P07, P08
---

## Section Purpose

The production section supports background artists and supervisors during active painting by providing structured checks at three critical quality gates — style consistency, missing detail identification, and asset documentation. 
Each prompt catches a different category of production error before it reaches the final review stage, reducing the volume and cost of late-stage rework. 
Together these three prompts create an auditable production record for every background that passes through the pipeline


## Chain Diagram 

```
Artist submits completed colour key background
      ↓
[P06 RUNS — checks background against style guide rules]
      ↓
PASS / CONDITIONAL PASS → continues
FAIL → returned to artist for revision
      ↓
[P07 RUNS — identifies missing or incomplete details]
      ↓
HIGH / MEDIUM issues → returned to artist for correction
LOW only or no issues → continues
      ↓
[P08 RUNS — generates structured asset documentation entry]
      ↓
Supervisor approves documentation → feeds into 04-review-handoff


